        browser, none of your financial numbers ever leave your device.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Capital gains tax is charged on the profit you make when you sell an
        asset for more than you paid for it. The taxable gain is generally your
        sale price minus your cost basis (purchase price plus eligible costs
        like improvements and selling fees). How that gain is taxed depends on
        two things: how long you held the asset and how much you earn. This
        <strong>2025 capital gains tax calculator</strong> handles both
        automatically, applying the correct short-term or long-term rate and
        layering in surtaxes and state or provincial taxes where they apply.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-2">
        Short-Term vs. Long-Term Capital Gains Tax
      </h3>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The single biggest factor in your bill is your holding period. As a
        <strong>short term capital gains tax calculator</strong>, this tool
        stacks gains from assets held one year or less on top of your ordinary
        income, so they are taxed at your marginal income rate &mdash; the
        <strong>short term capital gains tax rate</strong> can reach 37% for high
        earners. Switch the holding period to long-term and it becomes a
        <strong>long-term capital gains tax calculator</strong>, applying the
        preferential <strong>long term capital gains tax rate</strong> of 0%,
        15%, or 20% that rewards investors who hold for more than a year.
        Comparing the two side by side often reveals that waiting just a few
        extra weeks to cross the one-year mark can save thousands in tax.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-2">
        A Federal Capital Gains Tax Calculator by Income
      </h3>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Capital gains rates are tied to your income, which is why this is a true
        <strong>federal capital gains tax calculator</strong> and a
        <strong>capital gains tax calculator by income</strong>. Enter your
        annual ordinary income and filing status, and the estimator places your
        gain into the right band using the latest <strong>capital gains tax
        brackets 2025</strong>. It also adds the 3.8% Net Investment Income Tax
        (NIIT) once your modified adjusted gross income passes $200,000 (single)
        or $250,000 (married filing jointly), and applies state-level taxes so
        your estimate reflects your real, all-in <strong>capital gains tax</strong>
        liability rather than just the headline federal figure.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-2">
        Real Estate, Property & Rental Capital Gains
      </h3>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Selling a home or investment property has its own rules, so this doubles
        as a <strong>real estate capital gains tax calculator</strong>. Use it
        as a <strong>capital gains tax calculator on sale of property</strong> or
        a <strong>capital gains tax calculator on sale of rental property</strong>
        by selecting the Real Estate asset type, then add capital improvements
        and selling costs to raise your cost basis and reduce your taxable gain.
        Where a primary-residence exemption applies, you can toggle it on to see
        how much of your profit is shielded from tax. The result is an accurate
        estimate of the capital gains tax due on the sale of any property.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-2">
        How to Calculate Capital Gains Tax in Three Steps
      </h3>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
        To <strong>calculate capital gains tax</strong>, first enter your
        purchase and sale prices along with any improvements or selling fees.
        Second, choose your holding period and asset type so the tool knows
        whether to apply short- or long-term rates. Third, add your annual
        income and filing status so it can match your gain to the correct
        bracket. The <strong>capital gains calculator</strong> instantly returns
        your total gain, the tax owed, your effective rate, and a clear
        breakdown you can export to CSV or Excel. A what-if slider lets you test
        different sale prices so you can plan the most tax-efficient time to
        sell.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-2">
        Why Use This Investment Tax Calculator
